tempest/cmd/cleanup.py.message:
1) This doesn't really matter much, but it is possible to simply raise Exception on L116 immediately. That way, we terminate the for loop as soon as any exception is found.

Meaning:

    if not isinstance(ex, exceptions.NotImplemented):
        raise Exception(self.GOT_EXCEPTIONS)

2) Thinking further, this can still be improved further. That is because we are raising self.GOT_EXCEPTIONS -- which INCLUDES the NotImplementedError exceptions that we don't care about, which should be excluded from this list.

So, perhaps:

   critical_exceptions = []
   for ex in self.GOT_EXCEPTIONS:
        if not isinstance(ex, exceptions.NotImplemented):
            critical_exceptions.append(ex)
        if critical_exceptions:
            raise Exception(exceptions)

Which of course can be reduced further:

     critical_exceptions = [ex for ex in self.GOT_EXCEPTIONS if not isinstance(ex, NotImplementedError)]
      if critical_exceptions:
            raise Exception(exceptions)

